    "title": "The Earth is all That Lasts",
    "quote": {
        "source": {
            "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Black_Elk_Speaks",
            "title": "Black Elk Speaks",
            "author": "John G. Neihardt",
            "year": "1932"
        },
        "attribution": "Black Elk, 1932",
        "tags": ["First Nations", "Mythology", "Legends", "Death", "War"]
    },
    "photo": {
        "photographer": "Alexander Galea",
        "desc": "Distant mountain views as the light fades, from North of Vancouver way up in the sky",
        "date_taken": "October 2020",
        "location": "Crown Mountain",
        "tags": ["Hike", "Mountains", "Sunset"]
    },
    "cover_image": "1-20201007-IMG_7509.jpg",
    "body" : {
        "divs": [
            {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "I went into our tepee and got dressed for war as fast as I could; but I could hear bullets whizzing outside"
            },
            {
                "type": "photo",
                "file": "1-20201007-IMG_7509.jpg"
            },
            {
                "type": "photo",
                "file": "2-20201007-IMG_7511.jpg"
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "I was so shaky that it took me a long time to braid an eagle feather into my hair."
            },
            {
                "type": "photo",
                "file": "3-20201007-IMG_7536.jpg"
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "While I was doing this, crowds of warriors on horses were roaring by up stream, yelling: \"Hoka hey!\""
            },
            {
                "type": "photo",
                "file": "4-20201007-IMG_7523.jpg"
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Then I rubbed red paint all over my face and took my bow and arrows and got on my horse. I did not have a gun, only a bow and arrows."
            },
            {
                "type": "photo",
                "file": "5-20201007-IMG_7529.jpg"
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "A man by the name of Little Bear rode up to me on a pinto horse, and he had a very pretty saddle blanket."
            },
            {
                "type": "photo",
                "file": "6-20201007-IMG_7513-SMOOTH.jpg"
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "He said: \"Take courage, boy! The earth is all that lasts!\""
            }
        ]
    }
}